This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with depth estimation from single monocular images. The use of deep convolutional neural networks (CNN) and fully convolutional deep residual networks also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) categories. The application of fully-connected conditional random fields (CRF) as a post-processing step suggests that it could also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) category, as CRFs are commonly used in robotics for tasks such as object recognition and localization. Finally, the use of probability distributions to predict confidence levels suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) category, as probability distributions are commonly used in neural networks for tasks such as uncertainty estimation and regularization.
